	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have recently started camping Hadden and his really nifty earring and have a few words of advice for any one else looking for this very nice item.<BR>
<BR>
Word of advice 1.  Aggro.  His other buddies will aggro on you if you are a level 34 Shaman.  Found this out the hard way.  Hadden popped ( conned green ) and I hit him with a DOT and put my puppy on him.  Needless to say all hell broke loose.  My dog was taunting Hadden and Axe and Rephans Pet as Rephan stunned me over and over.  By the time the dust had settled there were 3 very satisfied Mobs standing around my body and the Pet was off chasing rabbits.  But all is not lost for those interested in camping the ear ring at my level or below.<BR>
<BR>
Word of Advice 2.  Lure.  If you have the spawn timed out then camping Hadden is pretty easy.  About 10 minutes before the time you think he is going to spawn, nuke Rephas with a low level low mana spell, then run like hell towards BB.  He will be casting at you and will hit you once or twice but with SOW you can easily out distance him.  Wait near the ruins until you see him coming, then gate back to Spawn point for Hadden.  Make your pet ( if applicable and med to full ).  Rephas will take 30 minutes to wander back to his spawn point.  When Hadden and Axe pop, fry em both and hope for some jewelry ( so far I have gotten a few nice rusty daggers ).<BR>
<BR>
Word of Advice 3.  Visibility.  Make sure you are clearly visible to any of the numerous people who have bound themselves there to pop in and check on Hadden.  I have never seen so many level 50 players in my life as I have during this camp.  None have tried to KS me and for that I am grateful.  The golden rule is in effect for the most part on Erollisi Marr.<BR>
<BR>
Shardmoon Totemwolf<BR>
34 Shaman
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
