	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok more data on this guy.<BR>
<BR>
I have camped and killed him a total of 72 times (boy is my butt sore).  During these 72 times, I collected a bunch of data.  Here is the results of the data:<BR>
<BR>
Average spawn time:  5 hours 40 minutes<BR>
Minimum spawn time:  5 hours 27 minutes<BR>
Maximum spawn time:  5 hours 55 minutes<BR>
<BR>
I suspect that its 5 hours 25 minutes plus a random number between 0 and 29 more minutes.<BR>
<BR>
I didn't collect fishbone earring drop information on all of the kills, only on the last 18 kills.  On these last 18 kills, 4 of them dropped the fishbone earring. There was no apparent pattern (not the every third one mentioned above).  Sometimes it was two in a row, sometimes it was nothing for 7 kills, then a fishbone.<BR>
<BR>
If you wish to camp this guy, make sure you know the previous time, then go there 1/2 hour before the next spawn (if in the wee hours of the morning) or 1 hour before the next spawn (if in a busy time of the day).  If you get there and somebody else is there, then they are camping him and you will have to wait for the next one.  Most people are only too happy to give out the timing information, if you are considerate and let them kill without being disturbed (or kill-stolen from).<BR>
<BR>
A trick that I discovered is this.  People often dual camp, they camp Pyzjin and Hadden in the same zone.  Since Pyzjin only spawns at night, they wait the night hours over at the ruins or at the entrance to BB.  During the day, they wait near Hadden's spawn point (right next to the hut on the lake).  If you go there to camp him, and you get there at night-time, chances are, that if there is somebody there dual-camping, you can sit down at the Hadden spawn point and claim it.  If you get there during the day, they might be there camping him already.  So my trick is to compute the time to arrive such that it is before the desired amount (1 hour, or 1/2 hour) and still during a night-time hour.  Little bit sneaky, but then so is dual-camping.<BR>
<BR>
I am beginning to think that there may be a quest which terminates at this guy (whereupon he gives you the fishbone earring), but I've reached mostly dead-ends so far.  Any help on exploring this would be appreciated.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
